Root Cause Analysis

The PHP code concatenates user input directly into the SQL query:
php

// Vulnerable code in DVWA
$id = $_GET['id'];
$query = "SELECT first_name, last_name FROM users WHERE user_id = $id";
$result = mysqli_query($GLOBALS["___mysqli_ston"], $query);

The application does NOT:

    Sanitize the user input

    Use parameterized queries

    Escape special characters

Business Impact

If this vulnerability existed in Meridian FinServe's customer portal:

    Data Breach: Attacker could extract all customer PII (names, addresses, financial data)

    Account Takeover: Bypass authentication and login as any user

    Regulatory Violations: RBI guidelines require data protection - breach would incur fines

    Reputational Damage: Loss of customer trust, negative media coverage

Remediation
Code Fix - Before (Vulnerable)
php

$id = $_GET['id'];
$query = "SELECT first_name, last_name FROM users WHERE user_id = $id";
$result = mysqli_query($conn, $query);

Code Fix - After (Secure)
php

$id = $_GET['id'];
$query = "SELECT first_name, last_name FROM users WHERE user_id = ?";
$stmt = $conn->prepare($query);
$stmt->bind_param("i", $id);
$stmt->execute();
$result = $stmt->get_result();

Why This Fix Works

    Prepared statements separate SQL logic from data

    Bind parameters ensure user input is treated as data, not executable code

    Even if an attacker injects SQL, it won't be executed

